WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.100 --> 00:00:08.102
(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:08.185 --> 00:00:09.979
♪ ♪

3
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

4
00:01:02.198 --> 00:01:03.991
♪ ♪

5
00:01:44.782 --> 00:01:47.201
Beric Dondarrion:
the wall Blackhaven

6
00:01:47.284 --> 00:01:50.246
are unscalable vassalstone.

7
00:01:51.747 --> 00:01:57.211
And the castle is surrounded
by a deep. dry moat.

8
00:01:57.294 --> 00:02:02.132
It is well fortified against
any future Dornish incursions.

9
00:02:02.216 --> 00:02:03.342
(chuckles)

10
00:02:03.425 --> 00:02:07.346
And though my seat
may be lesser in size.

11
00:02:07.429 --> 00:02:11.308
it is situated most pleasingly.

12
00:02:13.602 --> 00:02:15.563
(clears throat)

13
00:02:15.646 --> 00:02:16.689
(groans)

14
00:02:19.650 --> 00:02:21.694
(pouring wine)

15
00:02:23.821 --> 00:02:25.155
(light music playing)

16
00:02:30.828 --> 00:02:34.123
(thunder rumbling)

17
00:02:35.499 --> 00:02:39.795
The view across
the Marches is inspiring.

18
00:02:39.879 --> 00:02:41.022
so said Queen Alysanne herself

19
00:02:41.046 --> 00:02:43.757
when she honored
my father and I...

20
00:02:43.841 --> 00:02:46.302
And tell me. Lord Dondarrion.

21
00:02:46.385 --> 00:02:48.971
did you think my great-grandmother
as beautiful as they say?

22
00:02:50.264 --> 00:02:55.436
This was half
a century ago. Princess.

23
00:02:55.519 --> 00:02:57.146
Yes. it was.

24
00:02:57.229 --> 00:02:59.315
(crowd laughing)

25
00:02:59.398 --> 00:03:01.734
That was unseemly. Princess.

26
00:03:01.817 --> 00:03:04.486
The man is older than my father.

27
00:03:04.570 --> 00:03:06.822
It's unseemly for him
to put himself forward

28
00:03:06.906 --> 00:03:09.033
as a contender for my hand.

29
00:03:10.576 --> 00:03:11.702
Next!

30
00:03:15.372 --> 00:03:18.375
(thunder rumbling. wind gusting)

31
00:03:22.755 --> 00:03:25.132
And now a child.

32
00:03:25.215 --> 00:03:27.068
Boremund Baratheon: The
Blackwoods are an ancient house

33
00:03:27.092 --> 00:03:29.386
with a formidable army.

34
00:03:29.470 --> 00:03:33.682
In the Riverlands. they
once ruled as kings.

35
00:03:33.766 --> 00:03:37.144
The blood of the First
Men still flows in their veins.

36
00:03:39.438 --> 00:03:42.483
Go on.

37
00:03:42.566 --> 00:03:44.401
My Princess...

38
00:03:44.485 --> 00:03:46.320
ours is a bond that
has long endured.

39
00:03:46.403 --> 00:03:48.989
since Lucas Blackwood.
the grandsire of my grandsire.

40
00:03:49.073 --> 00:03:51.075
aided the Dragon in
his war of conquest...

41
00:03:51.158 --> 00:03:55.037
Aye. the Blackwoods truly
turned the tide on that one.

42
00:03:55.120 --> 00:03:57.498
(crowd laughing)

43
00:03:57.581 --> 00:03:59.333
Coursed with the
blood of the First Men.

44
00:03:59.416 --> 00:04:02.586
our history is deeply
rooted in this land.

45
00:04:02.670 --> 00:04:05.673
which your house
has made its home.

46
00:04:05.756 --> 00:04:06.983
If chosen as your
match. Princess...

47
00:04:07.007 --> 00:04:09.677
your days shall be easy

48
00:04:09.760 --> 00:04:13.013
and nights safe
under my protection.

49
00:04:13.097 --> 00:04:15.808
"Protection"? The Princess
has a dragon. you dumb cunt.

50
00:04:15.891 --> 00:04:18.435
(crowd laughing)

51
00:04:18.519 --> 00:04:20.020
Bracken!

52
00:04:20.104 --> 00:04:21.814
I could learn to like that one.

53
00:04:22.523 --> 00:04:25.275
Ugh. let us have the next

54
00:04:25.359 --> 00:04:27.486
so we may go to supper.

55
00:04:28.946 --> 00:04:31.031
- Craven.
- Crowd: Ooh!

56
00:04:32.825 --> 00:04:35.869
We're leaving.

57
00:04:36.620 --> 00:04:39.206
- Sheathe that steel. you twats!
- (grunting)

58
00:04:39.289 --> 00:04:42.084
Send word to the harbor and
have Captain Oswin ready the ship.

59
00:04:42.167 --> 00:04:43.853
Princess. we're due in
Bitterbridge in three days' time.

60
00:04:43.877 --> 00:04:45.730
I would happily row myself
back to King's Landing

61
00:04:45.754 --> 00:04:47.107
if it brought an end to
this ridiculous pageant.

62
00:04:47.131 --> 00:04:50.884
- (Bracken grunts)
- (crowd gasps)

63
00:04:53.429 --> 00:04:55.055
Don't look. Princess.

64
00:04:58.767 --> 00:05:00.811
♪ ♪

65
00:05:16.368 --> 00:05:19.329
We should make landfall
inside the hour. Princess.

66
00:05:22.583 --> 00:05:24.168
How do you think
he will take it?

67
00:05:24.251 --> 00:05:25.645
Do you speak of how
you rejected every suitor

68
00:05:25.669 --> 00:05:28.756
His Grace put before you. or
how you abruptly ended the tour

69
00:05:28.839 --> 00:05:30.090
with two months remaining?

70
00:05:33.469 --> 00:05:35.554
(dragon shrieking)

71
00:05:42.895 --> 00:05:44.480
(rumbling)

72
00:05:46.315 --> 00:05:48.275
(shouts) Take cover!

73
00:05:48.358 --> 00:05:48.817
(shrieks)

74
00:05:48.901 --> 00:05:52.154
(dramatic music playing)

75
00:05:52.738 --> 00:05:53.781
Princess!

76
00:05:54.907 --> 00:05:57.618
You all right? Are you?

77
00:05:57.701 --> 00:05:59.578
- Fetch the maester!
- I'm fine.

78
00:06:03.290 --> 00:06:04.875
(roars)

79
00:06:05.542 --> 00:06:07.336
♪ ♪

80
00:06:18.722 --> 00:06:21.225
(tense music playing)

81
00:06:29.024 --> 00:06:31.110
(indistinct chatter)

82
00:06:51.630 --> 00:06:53.215
Woman: (whispers) It's Daemon.

83
00:07:02.808 --> 00:07:04.017
♪ ♪

84
00:07:04.101 --> 00:07:07.271
(footsteps approach)

85
00:07:11.567 --> 00:07:13.152
(door opens)

86
00:07:15.779 --> 00:07:17.823
♪ ♪

87
00:07:45.350 --> 00:07:46.768
(swords unsheathing)

88
00:07:57.696 --> 00:07:59.406
- Add it to the chair.
- (clatters)

89
00:08:01.658 --> 00:08:03.577
(crowd murmuring)

90
00:08:15.464 --> 00:08:17.090
You wear a crown.

91
00:08:18.217 --> 00:08:19.927
Do you also call
yourself "King"?

92
00:08:20.969 --> 00:08:22.596
Once we smashed the Triarchy.

93
00:08:22.679 --> 00:08:25.599
they named me "King
of the Narrow Sea."

94
00:08:25.682 --> 00:08:27.517
(crowd murmuring)

95
00:08:29.895 --> 00:08:33.524
But I know that there is only
one true king. Your Grace.

96
00:08:36.902 --> 00:08:40.656
♪ ♪

97
00:08:42.074 --> 00:08:46.286
My crown and the
Stepstones... are yours.

98
00:08:50.249 --> 00:08:52.251
Well. where is Lord Corlys?

99
00:08:52.334 --> 00:08:53.543
He sailed home to Driftmark.

100
00:08:53.627 --> 00:08:57.673
- Who holds the Stepstones?
- Daemon: The tides...

101
00:08:57.756 --> 00:09:03.303
the crabs. and 2.000
dead Triarchy corsairs.

102
00:09:03.387 --> 00:09:06.556
staked to the sand to warn
those who might follow.

103
00:09:08.558 --> 00:09:10.602
♪ ♪

104
00:09:43.802 --> 00:09:45.137
Rise.

105
00:09:51.351 --> 00:09:52.602
♪ ♪

106
00:09:55.897 --> 00:09:57.691
(crowd applauds)

107
00:09:59.651 --> 00:10:02.529
(victorious music playing)

108
00:10:08.452 --> 00:10:11.830
The realm owes you
a great debt. brother.

109
00:10:14.958 --> 00:10:16.001
Come.

110
00:10:21.256 --> 00:10:23.550
This is our chance...

111
00:10:23.633 --> 00:10:26.136
Daemon. he would
venture off. abroad.

112
00:10:26.219 --> 00:10:29.056
winning tournaments...

113
00:10:31.058 --> 00:10:32.298
No. no. no. no. no. no. no. no.

114
00:10:32.351 --> 00:10:34.561
I will not revisit this debate.

115
00:10:34.644 --> 00:10:36.897
You were always
mother's favorite.

116
00:10:36.980 --> 00:10:39.066
No. it's no great mystery.

117
00:10:39.149 --> 00:10:41.360
You were.

118
00:10:41.443 --> 00:10:42.277
Our mother. she had no regard

119
00:10:42.361 --> 00:10:45.405
for custom or tradition. rules.

120
00:10:45.489 --> 00:10:49.326
And I. sadly. was
no great warrior.

121
00:10:49.409 --> 00:10:52.746
Congratulations on your victory.

122
00:10:57.250 --> 00:10:58.710
Thank you. Princess.

123
00:11:05.008 --> 00:11:07.636
Perhaps Prince Daemon would
care for a tour of the gallery?

124
00:11:07.719 --> 00:11:08.780
He hasn't yet seen
the new tapestries

125
00:11:08.804 --> 00:11:11.681
- gifted to you by Norvos and Qohor.
- Oh. oh.

126
00:11:11.765 --> 00:11:16.478
Would you like to see
the tapestries? (laughs)

127
00:11:16.561 --> 00:11:19.773
(snorts. laughs)

128
00:11:19.856 --> 00:11:22.526
He has no interest
in such things.

129
00:11:23.860 --> 00:11:26.279
I'd like to see them.

130
00:11:26.363 --> 00:11:29.324
Oh. well. then you
should not deprive yourself.

131
00:11:31.201 --> 00:11:33.078
I shall enjoy them alone.

132
00:11:36.373 --> 00:11:38.125
King Viserys: More wine.

133
00:11:41.711 --> 00:11:43.630
As I said. you
were the favorite.

134
00:11:43.713 --> 00:11:47.884
No. you were.
You were. I insist.

135
00:11:47.968 --> 00:11:49.553
(King Viserys laughs)

136
00:11:53.515 --> 00:11:56.017
- (indistinct chatter)
- (laughter continues)

137
00:12:03.233 --> 00:12:05.527
I surmise the tour
did not go well.

138
00:12:05.610 --> 00:12:07.010
I endured it for
as long as I could.

139
00:12:09.114 --> 00:12:10.383
To have every
young knight and lord

140
00:12:10.407 --> 00:12:13.827
in the Seven Kingdoms
fawning over you...

141
00:12:13.910 --> 00:12:16.955
What misery.

142
00:12:18.748 --> 00:12:22.419
It is rare for girls in this realm to
get a choice between two suitors.

143
00:12:22.502 --> 00:12:25.338
no less two score of them.

144
00:12:25.422 --> 00:12:28.633
Those men and boys
don't fawn over me.

145
00:12:28.717 --> 00:12:31.553
They only want my name and
my Valyrian blood for their offspring.

146
00:12:33.513 --> 00:12:36.391
I think it's rather romantic.

147
00:12:38.059 --> 00:12:41.354
How romantic it must be
to get imprisoned in a castle

148
00:12:41.438 --> 00:12:43.899
and made to squeeze out heirs.

149
00:12:47.194 --> 00:12:48.778
(sorrowful music playing)

150
00:12:48.862 --> 00:12:49.905
(softly) Sorry.

151
00:12:58.330 --> 00:13:00.790
How angry is he?

152
00:13:04.836 --> 00:13:07.255
The King went through great
effort to arrange your tour.

153
00:13:07.339 --> 00:13:10.967
He is... frustrated.

154
00:13:11.051 --> 00:13:13.595
But I am glad you are home.

155
00:13:13.678 --> 00:13:14.721
♪ ♪

156
00:13:16.848 --> 00:13:21.811
I find I have...
few friends lately.

157
00:13:21.895 --> 00:13:24.898
I like to believe I'm still
the Lady Alicent. but...

158
00:13:27.150 --> 00:13:31.154
all anyone sees when they
look at me now is "The Queen."

159
00:13:32.405 --> 00:13:35.242
I've missed you. too.

160
00:13:35.659 --> 00:13:38.328
♪ ♪

161
00:13:43.917 --> 00:13:45.835
(Rhaenyra speaking
High Valyrian)

162
00:14:10.193 --> 00:14:11.278
So...

163
00:14:12.779 --> 00:14:14.072
what do you want?

164
00:14:14.781 --> 00:14:16.783
Only the comforts of home.

165
00:14:24.583 --> 00:14:28.587
I had not thought you particularly
comfortable in this home.

166
00:14:31.506 --> 00:14:35.051
Though I do suppose you seem
changed by your adventures.

167
00:14:36.386 --> 00:14:38.805
More mature. perhaps.

168
00:14:40.640 --> 00:14:43.435
You've matured yourself
these last four years. Princess.

169
00:14:45.770 --> 00:14:47.897
You'll get used
to the attention.

170
00:14:47.981 --> 00:14:48.732
The attention I can endure.

171
00:14:48.815 --> 00:14:51.401
It's the rest I
could do without.

172
00:14:51.484 --> 00:14:53.403
My father seems
content to sell me off

173
00:14:53.486 --> 00:14:56.823
to whichever lord
has the biggest castle.

174
00:14:56.906 --> 00:14:59.492
There are worse
things to be sold for.

175
00:15:03.496 --> 00:15:07.125
(speaking High Valyrian)

176
00:15:27.562 --> 00:15:29.230
(Daemon laughs)

177
00:15:29.314 --> 00:15:31.775
Oh... (chuckles)

178
00:16:16.569 --> 00:16:20.031
Such a lonely prospect.

179
00:16:20.115 --> 00:16:21.783
(bell tolling)

180
00:16:21.866 --> 00:16:24.053
Tyland Lannister: The Stepstones
were meant to be won for the realm.

181
00:16:24.077 --> 00:16:26.454
but over the past few days.
it seems we have traded

182
00:16:26.538 --> 00:16:28.832
a crabfeeder for a seasnake.

183
00:16:28.915 --> 00:16:33.503
This is clearly a rebuke for passing
over Lady Laena for Queen Alicent.

184
00:16:33.586 --> 00:16:36.548
Years have passed since
the business with his daughter.

185
00:16:36.631 --> 00:16:38.633
Certainly. he
cannot still be wroth?

186
00:16:38.717 --> 00:16:42.637
The Sea Snake is an over-proud
man. to be sure. Your Grace.

187
00:16:42.721 --> 00:16:44.764
That pride has been injured.

188
00:16:44.848 --> 00:16:47.767
Perhaps we can salve the wound?

189
00:16:47.851 --> 00:16:50.103
I fear Lord Corlys's pride
is the least of our worries.

190
00:16:50.186 --> 00:16:52.897
I don't wish to cause
you further distress.

191
00:16:52.981 --> 00:16:57.110
Your Grace. but my brother has
sent disturbing word from Oldtown.

192
00:16:57.193 --> 00:17:00.488
Lord Corlys is said to have
engaged in negotiations

193
00:17:00.572 --> 00:17:01.781
with the Sealord of Braavos.

194
00:17:01.865 --> 00:17:05.994
He plans to wed his daughter
Laena to the Sealord's son.

195
00:17:08.038 --> 00:17:11.416
If House Velaryon
entered into an alliance

196
00:17:11.499 --> 00:17:14.335
with the Free Cities...

197
00:17:14.419 --> 00:17:16.337
then...

198
00:17:16.421 --> 00:17:20.383
we would have to seek
our own marriage pact.

199
00:17:22.177 --> 00:17:24.012
(tense music playing)

200
00:17:36.191 --> 00:17:37.984
(baby wailing)

201
00:18:00.381 --> 00:18:02.217
(wailing continues)

202
00:18:09.432 --> 00:18:12.435
- Good night. Ser Criston.
- Sleep well. Princess.

203
00:18:17.857 --> 00:18:19.192
(exhales)

204
00:18:45.426 --> 00:18:46.678
(sniffs)

205
00:18:57.480 --> 00:18:59.107
(uneasy music playing)

206
00:19:26.676 --> 00:19:29.721
Whoa!

207
00:19:35.894 --> 00:19:37.937
♪ ♪

208
00:20:21.356 --> 00:20:23.191
(breathing heavily)

209
00:20:28.154 --> 00:20:29.197
♪ ♪

210
00:20:32.575 --> 00:20:34.452
Rhaenyra: Where are we going?

211
00:20:39.707 --> 00:20:42.543
(people screaming)

212
00:20:42.919 --> 00:20:45.088
(laughs)

213
00:20:48.216 --> 00:20:50.176
♪ ♪

214
00:20:52.220 --> 00:20:54.055
(moaning)

215
00:20:59.310 --> 00:21:01.270
- Drunkard: Fuck off. boy.
- (Rhaenyra gasps)

216
00:21:03.356 --> 00:21:04.691
He called me boy.

217
00:21:08.444 --> 00:21:10.029
(laughter)

218
00:21:15.660 --> 00:21:17.578
♪ ♪

219
00:21:23.292 --> 00:21:24.210
(coughs)

220
00:21:24.293 --> 00:21:27.088
Do you wish to know
your death. child?

221
00:21:32.218 --> 00:21:35.471
(King Viserys breathing heavily)

222
00:21:44.981 --> 00:21:46.607
Let me take that.

223
00:22:00.997 --> 00:22:03.332
Leave us. all of you.

224
00:22:21.434 --> 00:22:25.229
You have a far kinder
touch than they do.

225
00:22:25.313 --> 00:22:26.689
Thank you. husband.

226
00:22:28.858 --> 00:22:35.198
Player: <i>And now we come to
the matter of the great Iron Chair...</i>

227
00:22:35.948 --> 00:22:39.243
and whose bum it might bear.

228
00:22:39.327 --> 00:22:41.204
Our good King...

229
00:22:41.287 --> 00:22:42.789
names his daughter.

230
00:22:42.872 --> 00:22:45.917
a girl. his heir.

231
00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:48.461
(crowd jeering. booing)

232
00:22:50.046 --> 00:22:53.674
But then to him. a babe is born.

233
00:22:53.758 --> 00:22:55.593
(grunting)

234
00:22:56.969 --> 00:22:58.596
(groaning)

235
00:23:02.558 --> 00:23:04.936
- A son!
- (gasps)

236
00:23:05.019 --> 00:23:09.482
- (crowd cheering) - To which
heir might the chair bear?

237
00:23:09.565 --> 00:23:10.817
Who will it be?

238
00:23:10.900 --> 00:23:12.235
The brother? The daughter?

239
00:23:12.318 --> 00:23:14.695
Or the little
princeling of three?

240
00:23:14.779 --> 00:23:16.364
(laughter)

241
00:23:19.742 --> 00:23:22.245
(crying)

242
00:23:27.166 --> 00:23:31.420
Rhaenyra... the Realm's Delight.

243
00:23:31.504 --> 00:23:34.340
a girl so young and so slight...

244
00:23:35.341 --> 00:23:38.553
loved by all of her people.

245
00:23:38.636 --> 00:23:42.390
but would she make
a powerful queen.

246
00:23:42.473 --> 00:23:44.350
- or would she be feeble?
- Crowd: Feeble!

247
00:23:44.433 --> 00:23:47.019
Player: Though
Aegon. the babe Prince.

248
00:23:47.103 --> 00:23:49.021
might long for a claim.

249
00:23:49.105 --> 00:23:52.108
he has two things
Rhaenyra cannot:

250
00:23:52.191 --> 00:23:53.359
a conqueror's name...

251
00:23:54.944 --> 00:23:56.237
and a cock.

252
00:23:57.155 --> 00:23:58.865
(crowd cheering)

253
00:23:59.365 --> 00:24:01.367
Lies. slander!

254
00:24:01.450 --> 00:24:02.452
Boo!

255
00:24:02.535 --> 00:24:04.245
Jest if you will.

256
00:24:04.328 --> 00:24:06.247
but many of the
smallfolk are like to believe

257
00:24:06.330 --> 00:24:09.375
that. as a male. Aegon
should be the heir.

258
00:24:09.458 --> 00:24:12.712
Mm. Their wants are
of no consequence.

259
00:24:12.795 --> 00:24:15.673
- (Daemon laughs) -
(crowd cheering. whistling)

260
00:24:15.756 --> 00:24:16.966
They're of great consequence

261
00:24:17.049 --> 00:24:19.218
if you expect to
rule them one day.

262
00:24:20.845 --> 00:24:22.221
For one night. I wish to be free

263
